00:41:09,420 --> 00:41:11,920
The first hostage from Cornwall, the second from London,

678
00:41:11,920 --> 00:41:13,250
the third from Yorkshire, judging by her accent.

679
00:41:13,250 --> 00:41:16,060
What's he doing? Working his way round the world, showing off?

680
00:41:19,460 --> 00:41:24,260
You're enjoying this, aren't you?

681
00:41:25,820 --> 00:41:28,900
'Joining the...dots.'

682
00:41:31,180 --> 00:41:32,700
Three hours.

683
00:41:36,380 --> 00:41:40,180
Boom... boom.

684
00:41:52,100 --> 00:41:55,180
- We're devastated.  - Of course we are.

685
00:41:58,940 --> 00:42:00,660
Can I get you anything, sir?

686
00:42:00,660 --> 00:42:02,220
Er, no. No, thanks.

687
00:42:04,900 --> 00:42:08,740
Raoul is my rock. I don't think I could have managed.

688
00:42:10,620 --> 00:42:15,610
We didn't always see eye to eye... but my sister was very dear to me.

689
00:42:16,260 --> 00:42:19,820
And to the, er, public, Mr Prince.

690
00:42:19,820 --> 00:42:22,860
Oh, she was adored.

691
00:42:22,860 --> 00:42:26,540
I've seen her take girls who looked like the back end of Routemasters

692
00:42:26,540 --> 00:42:29,020
and turn them into princesses.

693
00:42:29,020 --> 00:42:30,420
Still, it's a relief, in a way,

694
00:42:30,420 --> 00:42:34,540
to know that she's beyond this vale of tears.

695
00:42:34,540 --> 00:42:37,260
Absolutely.

696
00:42:37,260 --> 00:42:39,260
Great.

697
00:42:39,260 --> 00:42:40,900
Thank you. Thanks again.

